## Port type connectability (Studio catalog)

When both ends of a drag resolve to a `StudioNodePortValueType` (YAML catalog and/or handle `portValueType`), **`studioPortValueTypesConnectable`** in `ui/editor/nodeHelpers.ts` is the rule:

- Same type → connectable (e.g. audio-to-audio, float-to-float, trigger-to-trigger).
- `int` ↔ `float` → connectable (numeric CV).

`tryCatalogPortConnection` runs **before** legacy `isAudioConnection` so named audio inputs (e.g. `sidechainIn`) match catalog audio ports the same way as `in`/`out`.

If catalog types disagree, `tryCatalogPortConnection` returns `null` and **`canConnect`** may still allow edges via legacy rules (e.g. LFO `out` typed `audio` in YAML into float modulation targets). Do not remove those paths without replacing them with explicit compatibility rules.
